reviews.review_text: my first experience..... ....and boy was it great. I`ve read a few reviews of this show and some people didn`t see the same show i saw! i`ll agree some nights the music wasn`t "on",but i`ve never seen what i`d say was a bad show. If you can`t tell me you didn`t get that "feeling",the feeling no one can describe when you went to a show,somethings wrong with you! Anyway,Half-Step opened the night...i still can see them as they broke into their dance...a charming Althea rippled through the evening then a jammin` Cumberland Blues made your feet move!they went to break with an incredible Promised Land that left us yearning for more...as we rose from the grass, the stadium could hardly hold the energy as those few chords danced off Jerry`s guitar...China-Rider tickeled our ears into a frenzy. The set rolled on...a beautiful Wharf Rat put us in awh...I still recall helping a friend build sand castles in the grass,eventhough there`s no sand on the 30 yard line at RFK,lol...The Weight ended the journey but started something i`ll never take back!! I stayed on till the music stopped in 95. That night started memories of a wonderful time in my life....i miss you.

What goes up must come down I remember the little Pamphlets going around the parking lot before the show. Skeletons dancing on thru the whole sheet. Going down that road for my second time ever. Jerry, Bobby, and Phil bathed in lights. Who was that girl, Next to me in the crowd? Thank you! Thank you for holding me thru the earthshaking and sky falling. Our fingers danced together thru "rider," danced right thru on fire. Too Far away to remember your number. You will always be my "Althea"
